<h1 align="center">A cubic curve through nine points</h1>

<p align="right"><a href="../index.html">Back to Geometry homepage</a></p>

The following diagram shows a cubic curve passing through nine points \(A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,I\) in the plane. By moving these points around you can see how the curve changes. <br /><br />

This construction uses the paper <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/30079781">Ruler Constructions in Connexion with Cubic Curves</a> by Robert Russell, and builds on the work of Chu Khoon Hwa's honours thesis.<br /><br />

